## Required Plugins

- **superpowers** (`obra/superpowers`) — provides `/writing-plans`, `/brainstorming`, `/executing-plans`, and plan-mode workflow support. Install: `claude plugin install obra/superpowers`
  - **Plan & spec location (overrides plugin default):** plans → `.superpowers/plans/`, specs → `.superpowers/specs/` (project-root, gitignored). Do NOT write under `docs/superpowers/` — `docs/` stays human-curated. Enforced by `.claude/hooks/superpowers-plan-location.sh`.
- **Code-intelligence LSP** (`claude-plugins-official`) — `pyright-lsp` (Python) + `clangd-lsp` (C/C++): go-to-definition, find-references, post-edit diagnostics via `.claude/settings.json` `enabledPlugins`, replacing grep-then-read sweeps. ⚠️ Without a `compile_commands.json`, clangd reports **false** errors on C/C++ (missing headers, unknown macros) — ignore those diagnostics or generate a compile DB. Binary prereqs, collaborator enablement, and setup: `.claude/rules/tech-stack.md`.
- **ponytail** (`DietrichGebert/ponytail`) — "lazy senior dev" optimization plugin (YAGNI, stdlib-first, no unrequested abstractions). Enabled by default via `.claude/settings.json` `enabledPlugins` + `extraKnownMarketplaces` (third-party marketplace, so it must be declared there — unlike the official-marketplace LSP plugins); fresh checkouts are zero-touch. Costs ~904 always-on tok/session and **intentionally overlaps** the always-loaded Karpathy guidelines (`engineering-principles.md`). Needs Node.js on PATH for its hooks. Remove the `enabledPlugins` line to opt out. Manual install: `claude plugin marketplace add DietrichGebert/ponytail` + `claude plugin install ponytail@ponytail`.
